{"uid":"174ad293a3bf325c","name":"test_patch_rename_tag_cascades_into_events_auto_tags","fullName":"tests.test_admin_catalog.TestAdminPatch#test_patch_rename_tag_cascades_into_events_auto_tags","historyId":"3f41a1da5e66c5f138c17e10900bc661","time":{"start":1777231834319,"stop":1777231834338,"duration":19},"description":"Renaming a tag via PATCH must rewrite every ``events.auto_tags``\nentry that references the old name.\n\n``auto_tags`` stores tag *names* (not ids) so the JSON value is\nstable across seed rebuilds that renumber ids, but that means a\nplain ``UPDATE tags SET name = ?`` would silently break the\nauto-attach pipeline: the next ``resolve_event_auto_tag_ids``\ncall would log an \"unknown tag name\" WARN and drop the tag\nfrom every new expense created under that event. The cascade\nkeeps auto-attach behaviour identical across the rename.\n","descriptionHtml":"<p>Renaming a tag via PATCH must rewrite every <code>events.auto_tags</code><br />\nentry that references the old name.</p>\n<p><code>auto_tags</code> stores tag <em>names</em> (not ids) so the JSON value is<br />\nstable across seed rebuilds that renumber ids, but that means a<br />\nplain <code>UPDATE tags SET name = ?</code> would silently break the<br />\nauto-attach pipeline: the next <code>resolve_event_auto_tag_ids</code><br />\ncall would log an &quot;unknown tag name&quot; WARN and drop the tag<br />\nfrom every new expense created under that event. The cascade<br />\nkeeps auto-attach behaviour identical across the rename.</p>\n","status":"passed","flaky":false,"newFailed":false,"newBroken":false,"newPassed":false,"retriesCount":0,"retriesStatusChange":false,"beforeStages":[{"name":"tmp_path_factory","time":{"start":1777231833205,"stop":1777231833206,"duration":1},"status":"passed","steps":[],"attachments":[],"parameters":[],"shouldDisplayMessage":false,"attachmentsCount":0,"stepsCount":0,"hasContent":false,"attachmentStep":false},{"name":"_disable_sheet_mapping_preload","time":{"start":17